## 1. Simulation Scope & Objectives

### What We're Simulating
We're creating a **miniature version** of the AURORA network that demonstrates:
- ✅ **Segmentation** - Multiple VLANs with different security zones
- ✅ **Traffic Flow** - Inter-VLAN routing with firewall rules
- ✅ **SIEM Integration** - Centralized logging and monitoring
- ✅ **Attack Simulation** - Kali Linux performing reconnaissance and exploitation
- ✅ **Endpoint Monitoring** - Windows 11 as a target with Wazuh agent

### What We're NOT Simulating
- ❌ External internet connectivity (BSI perimeter)
- ❌ Basel branch WAN link
- ❌ High-performance lab (resource constraints)
- ❌ Physical switches (using Alpine Linux virtual switches)

